OL,3,CWhale song has its own 'phonetic
OL,4,Calphabet', research shows
OL,6,FSperm whale calls are so complex they
OL,7,Fare comparable to the human language,
OL,8,Fscientists have discovered.
OL,10,FThe claim is based on the analysis of
OL,11,Fthousands of snippets of whale clicks
OL,12,F- known as codas - by scientists
OL,13,Fstudying the animals around the island
OL,14,Fof Dominica in the Caribbean.
OL,16,FThey found the whales use a sort of
OL,17,F"phonetic alphabet", enabling them
OL,18,Fcreate building blocks of language
OL,19,Fsimilar to words and phrases.
