OL,3,CWhale song has its own 'phonetic
OL,4,Calphabet', research shows
OL,6,FSperm whales communicate by squeezing
OL,7,Fair through their respiratory systems
OL,8,Fto make strings of rapid clicks.
OL,10,FScientists have been trying for
OL,11,Fdecades to understand what the clicks
OL,12,Fmight mean.
OL,14,FBut according to Jeremy Goldbogen, an
OL,15,Fassociate professor of oceans at
OL,16,FStanford University, this new research
OL,17,Fmay have "vast implications" for how
OL,18,Fwe understand the creatures.
