OL,3,CWhale song has its own 'phonetic
OL,4,Calphabet', research shows
OL,6,FThe scientists say they have found
OL,7,Ffour basic components they think make
OL,8,Fup the whales' phonetic alphabet. This
OL,9,Falphabet can then be used by the
OL,10,Fwhales in an unlimited number of
OL,11,Fcombinations - similarly to how words
OL,12,Fare used by humans.
OL,14,FThe whales also vary the rhythm and
OL,15,Ftempo of their clicks, adding an extra
OL,16,Flayer of complexity and meaning.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/6
