OL,3,CWhale song has its own 'phonetic
OL,4,Calphabet', research shows
OL,6,FTags on the whales also record what
OL,7,Fposition they are in while clicking -
OL,8,Ffor example diving, sleeping, or
OL,9,Fbreathing at the surface - and whether
OL,10,Fother whales are nearby.
OL,12,FScientists hope they will one day be
OL,13,Fable to understand what sperm whales
OL,14,Fare trying to communicate. That
OL,15,Fknowledge could be used for
OL,16,Fconservation purposes, like minimising
OL,17,Ftheir risk of being hit by ships or
OL,18,Freducing ocean noise levels.
